        <h2 class="color-faint" data-reveal>About</h2>
        <p data-reveal>Hi, I'm Codrin, as in /coh-dreen/.</p>
        <p data-reveal>I've been building websites commercially since 2009, mostly for creative agencies and media publishers.</p>
        <p data-reveal>Over the last 17 years I've delivered nearly 100 projects.</p>
        <p data-reveal>I care less about frameworks and more about shipping fast, accessible websites that make your agency look good. I enjoy taking polished Figma files and turning them into production-ready websites, working closely with designers to refine the details along the way.</p>
        <p data-reveal>For the last eight years I've focused on annual reports, ESG reports and corporate communications, projects that have gone on to win industry awards, earn excellent client feedback and launch on schedule.</p>

        <h2 data-reveal class="mt-6xl color-faint">Communication</h2>
        <p data-reveal>You'll always know what's happening and where the project stands.</p>
        <p data-reveal>Whether we're in design reviews, development, QA, launch week or post-launch edits, I'll be there when you need me. I'm comfortable working directly with clients or staying behind the scenes as part of your team — that's entirely your choice.</p>

        <h2 data-reveal class="mt-6xl color-faint">Working Hours</h2>
        <p data-reveal>I understand agency work isn't always predictable. Early launches happen, clients change their minds, or someone remembers that one last thing on the Friday before launch.</p>
        <p data-reveal>I'm used to it. I expect it. I'm only sometimes surprised when it doesn't happen. I've spent most of my career working US hours from Europe, so late evenings are just part of my routine. In 17 years, I've never missed a deadline.</p>

        <h2 data-reveal class="mt-6xl color-faint">Process</h2>
        <p data-reveal>Every agency has its own way of working and I've become used to adapting. If you already have a process, I'll fit into it. If you don't, that's fine too. I self-manage well and don't need much hand-holding.</p>
        <p data-reveal>I'm probably one of the few frontend developers who actually enjoys keeping project boards tidy. I keep tickets up to date, create missing ones when needed and generally leave the board in a better state than I found it.</p>

        <h2 data-reveal class="mt-6xl color-faint">Budget</h2>
        <p data-reveal>My approach is to find the version of the project that works for your agency within your client's budget.</p>
        <p data-reveal>Small technical decisions can have a big impact on cost. We'll work together to simplify, remove or optimise where it makes sense, without compromising the final result.</p>

        <h2 data-reveal class="mt-6xl color-faint">What I'm Looking For</h2>
        <p data-reveal>I'm looking for long-term design agency partners, especially teams working on annual reports, corporate communications and other content-rich microsites. I enjoy working with detail-oriented designers and content strategists. We tend to care about the same things: clarity, consistency and getting the details right.</p>
        <p data-reveal>If that sounds like your kind of team, I'd love to hear from you.</p>
